text: my thanks to mr. tim coleman for the sample .12oz cap bottle a : familiar amber-orange-gold rimmed glass of ipa beauty .a smallish white head form and then wind down , leave a soft line of whip egg white lace , a thin r.a.t.r. , and some float island .n : lovely and strong orange and grapefruit-leaning citrus hop in the nose , not too dis-similer to dfh 90 minute .a little dopiness here , with some marmalade and orange hard candy there .p : initial burst of the above describe hop , with a direct fresh bitterness to match .however , this be wash away somewhat by the lack of a backbone or back palate to back up thiw burst of flavor .almost like a fresh water rush , clear out the hop and bitterness remnant as they pass through you mouth , or rather like hold a gulp of dfh 90 in you mouth and follow it through with some evian .carbonation be present but very soft , and while the finish on one level stay firm and keep a linger presence , on the other the break be crisp be clean .this be a very odd combination overall , since it present two alternate universe simulaniously .nothing here be out of balance , but it be not quite yin yang either .the clean and wash out presence , however , turn into more of a empty space/void in the plate as the brew warm .note : i could definately see how some folk would like this : all the hop presence and flavor without that heavy mouthfeel or cloying aftertaste .however , it be that very same line of thought that bring we into the wonderful world of `` taste great-less fill '' and its horrifying permutation .i be not say that this be a ipa for miller lite drinker , but the palate do seem to present itself as a ipa with training wheel , if you will .the nose , however , be definately worth you time .i would still have one of these over a harpoon ipa anyday , though .-lrb- music : mile davi `` get up with it '' -rrb-

text: pour from 22oz brown bomber into a duvel tulip .best by apr 2013 stamp on card .purchase at beer run -lrb- charlottesville , va -rrb- for $ 11.99 .a : fairly dark amber with 1-finger off-white almost apricot head with average retention and a few tongue of lace .s : the aroma be kind of dank with a woody , sour apple note that hang over all of the light fruity pear and apricot note which be not subtle .i do not know if the sour note come from the yeast , the fermentation , fusel , or the conditioning on pine resin but it do not work for I on any level .t : the flavor carry forward the same dank , sour , woody note from the aroma which combine with a fairly alcoholic and sweet base .the maltiness be caramelly with some bready character .the ester be varied and interesting with lot of floral , pear , and apricot note .the sour note unfortunately cloud it all and cast a pall on what might otherwise be a pretty interesting beer .m : very smooth with controlled carbonation and a very full body with a dry , crisp finish .o : a very disappointing beer after revel in embrasse .this beer definitely need time to calm but i be not sure it will still be to my taste as i think the sour woody character will continue to dominate the otherwise interesting and lively fruity quality .far too woody and alcoholic to be a good tripel at this stage -- i have serious doubt , no matter how much brown paper they put on the bottle that this will be a beer i would enjoy .
